Since you’re on Arch, you likely used the AUR or NPM. On Arch, "apps" aren't always in your desktop menu; they often live in the terminal.

1. Google Gemini (CLI)
Google's official "app" for Linux is primarily the Gemini CLI.

Check if installed
Run these in your terminal:

which gemini (Should return a path like /usr/bin/gemini or ~/.npm-global/bin/gemini)

gemini --version

How to Install (if missing)
The standard way is via NPM:

Bash
npm install -g @google/gemini-cli
Alternatively, via the AUR: yay -S gemini-cli

How to Run
Simply type:

Bash
gemini
Note: First-time use requires a Google login via the browser or an API key from Google AI Studio.

2. Claude Code (CLI)
Anthropic’s Claude Code is a terminal-based agent. It is not the same as the Claude Desktop app (which is unofficial on Linux).

Check if installed
Run:

which claude

claude --version

How to Install (if missing)
The official recommended method is the native installer:

Bash
curl -fsSL https://claude.ai/install.sh | bash
Alternatively, via the AUR: yay -S claude-code

How to Run
Navigate to a project directory and type:

Bash
claude
Note: You must have a Claude Pro subscription or an Anthropic Console account with credits to use this.

3. "I can't find them" (Troubleshooting)
If the commands above return "command not found" but you’re sure you installed them via NPM, your PATH is likely the culprit.

Check your NPM global bin:
npm config get prefix

Add it to your shell config (.bashrc or .zshrc):

Bash
export PATH=$PATH:$(npm config get prefix)/bin
Reload your shell: source ~/.bashrc (or .zshrc).

Desktop Apps (GUIs)
If you are looking for graphical windows (icons in your app drawer):

Gemini: There is no official Google desktop app. You likely installed gemini-desktop from the AUR or Snap. Try running gemini-desktop in the terminal.

Claude: Install claude-desktop-bin from the AUR. You can then run it with the command claude-desktop.

